# Story 5.4 (Epic 5, llm-service): cinterop .def for the real FoundationModelsShim, extending
# Story 5.2's PingShim.def pattern (now proven in shape, though still unverified in this
# environment — see below) rather than starting cinterop-authoring from zero.
#
# Binds against FoundationModelsShim's Clang module (Xcode auto-generates its module map +
# -Swift.h interface header when the FoundationModelsShim Xcode framework target builds —
# see iosApp/README.md for the exact xcodebuild invocation that must run BEFORE this cinterop
# task runs). The `-F<path>` framework search path is supplied per-target from
# kmp/build.gradle.kts's `cinterops { create("FoundationModelsShim") { compilerOpts(...) } }`
# block, not hardcoded here.
#
# NOT verified in this environment (Linux sandbox, no Xcode/cinterop toolchain available) —
# see Task 5.4c in iosApp/README.md for the required manual "real gate" build verification.

language = Objective-C
modules = FoundationModelsShim
package = shim.foundationmodels
